## M22: unsafe builtins outside a `raw` block are rejected.
##
## Per GPT-5.5 entry 35 (M21 design): builtin classification is
## default-unsafe with a small safe whitelist. Pointer
## manipulation (`@ptrCast`, `@intFromPtr`, `@ptrFromInt`,
## `@memcpy`, `@bitCast`, etc.) is unsafe by default — any of
## these outside a `raw` block fires a tailored diagnostic
## naming the specific builtin and listing the safe whitelist.

sub main()
  x = 42
  y = @ptrCast(x)            # error: unsafe builtin outside `raw` block
